This is PingBox — a WhatsApp-inspired distributed messaging system.

Tech stack:
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.13), WebSockets, PostgreSQL, Redis, MinIO
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Auth: JWT (access + refresh tokens)
- Real-time: WebSockets via FastAPI
- Object storage: MinIO (S3-compatible)
- Cache: Redis (presence, TTL, rate limiting)
- Package manager: uv (not pip)
- Containerization: Docker Compose

Conventions:
- All backend code lives in backend/app/
- Use async/await everywhere in FastAPI
- SQLAlchemy async ORM for database models
- Pydantic v2 for schemas
- Environment variables via pydantic-settings
- Never hardcode secrets
- Every router has its own file in routers/
- WebSocket connection manager lives in ws/manager.py

Current phase: Phase 1 — Auth + real-time messaging + ACK chain

CRITICAL RULES - NEVER VIOLATE:
- NEVER auto-edit or rewrite these files unless explicitly told to:
  * app/main.py
  * app/core/config.py
  * app/core/security.py
- NEVER change uppercase settings keys to lowercase
- NEVER switch DATABASE_URL to sqlite
- NEVER add new routers to main.py automatically
- ALWAYS ask before modifying any existing working file
- ONLY create or edit files that are explicitly requested